#' Example dataset of loPCA() result
#'
#' A list-type dataset containing results from the 4-steps local PCA procedure from Li and Ralph (2019).
#' The variables are as follows:
#'
#' \itemize{
#'   \item winfun. Function generated by lostruct::vcf_windower() to divide SNP data into windows of fixed size (here 100-SNPs windows)
#'   \item pcs_all. Matrix with 757 obs. (genomic windows) of 255 variables (PCA coordinates from first 2 PCs for each of the 126 samples) generated by lostruct::eigen_windows()
#'   \item rows_na. Indices of rows containing NA in pcs_all
#'   \item pcs. Same as pcs_all, but excluding rows_na (identical to pcs_all if rows_na=0)
#'   \item pcdist. Dissimilarity matrix of 757x757 obs. (numeric values) generated by lostruct::pc_dist()
#'   \item fit2d. List of 5 variables generated by lostruct::cmdscale() that summarize pcdist across 40 MDS
#'   \item data. Data frame with 757 obs. (genomic windows) of 44 variables
#' }
#'
#' @name winList
#' @docType data
#' @keywords datasets
#' @usage data(winList)
#' @format A list of 7 variables
NULL




#' Example outlier regions obtained with getRegion()
#'
#' A list-type dataset containing 7 or 8 output variables from the function getRegion().
#' The output variables are as follows:
#'
#' \itemize{
#'   \item wins. Data frame with 757 obs. of 4 variables
#'   \item coor.raw. Data frame with 757 obs. (genomic windows) of 40 variables (MDS) containing raw MDS coordinate values
#'   \item coor.cr. Data frame with 757 obs. (genomics windows) of 40 variables (MDS) containing centered-reducted MDS coordinate values
#'   \item pval. Data frame with 757 obs. (genomic windows) of 40 variables (MDS) containing p-values from normal distribution of coor.cr data
#'   \item fdr. Data frame with 757 obs. (genomic windows) of 40 variables (MDS) containing FDR rejection test result based on p-values data
#'   \item tabF_raw. Pre-final data frame with 12 obs. (outlier genomic regions) of 7 variables (ID, MDS, chr, start, end, noutliers, SizeRegions). Present only concat_redundant=TRUE, otherwise this data frame is stored as tabF
#'   \item tabF. Final data frame with 7 obs. (outlier genomic regions) of 8 variables (nID, ID, MDS, chr, start, end, noutliers, SizeRegions). Outlier regions are corrected for redundancy if concat_redundant=TRUE (here TRUE)
#'   \item listRegionWin. List of genomic window indices for each of the outlier genomic regions detected (here 12)
#' }
#'
#' @name regList
#' @docType data
#' @keywords datasets
#' @usage data(regList)
#' @format A list of 8 variables
NULL




#' Example dataset of detectInv() result
#'
#' A list-type dataset containing sub-lists of 4 variables for each outlier regions analysed.
#' The variables within each sub-list are as follows:
#'
#' \itemize{
#'   \item mat. Data frame with 126 obs. of 12 variables (sample.id, pop, pop.cols, group, cluster, group.cols, PC1, PC2, PC3, het.nsites, het.obs, het.exp)
#'   \item pca.var. Numerical vector [1:3] containing precentage of explained variance on the first three PCs
#'   \item het.wilcox.test. Rstatix_test class object containing result from wilcoxon test
#'   \item het.bonf.corr. Numeric list containing Bonferroni-corrected p-values for significance levels \*, \*\* and \*\*\*
#' }
#'
#' @name invList
#' @docType data
#' @keywords datasets
#' @usage data(invList)
#' @format A list of 7 variables
NULL
